content: Tell me about an assumption or belief you recently discarded after stress-testing it.
What's a random, small thing that gave you an unexpected hit of joy lately?
What did you dream of inventing or exploring as a kid? How does that connect to who you are today?
What's a lucky break or unexpected opportunity you're grateful for?
If you're open to sharing, what's a problem that won't leave you alone right now?
Is there a practice or constraint that's actually helped focus your scattered energy?
What's the next thing you want to figure out or experiment with, just for the fun of it?
Describe your ideal day of interesting problems and good conversation.
You're having drinks with anyone from history. Whose brain would you most want to pick?
Who is someone who challenged you in a way that actually upgraded your thinking?
What's something you used to be fascinated by that you've moved on from?
Right now, what idea or project has your attention locked in?
Describe a time when you were completely in your element—what made that click?
What's a concept, book, or debate that permanently changed how you see things?
Looking ahead one year, what new capability or insight do you want to develop?
Tell me about a favor or gesture from someone that stuck with you more than expected.
Is there a dilemma you're currently arguing both sides of in your head?
What's an unconventional approach you take that others find confusing?
What's a piece of counterintuitive wisdom that's served you well?
What's one thing you feel is commonly misunderstood about you, based on your debating or joking?
How has your definition of 'winning at life' changed over time?
Can you think of an experience that forced you to completely reframe your understanding?
What's something you're proud of that doesn't fit the typical success narrative?
When you think of the people worth your time, what makes someone interesting enough to engage with?
Tell me about a fear you've talked yourself through or faced head-on.
When you're scattered or stuck, what gets you back on track?
What's a view you hold that you enjoy defending against popular opinion?
What's captured your curiosity or sparked new connections lately?
Think about a failure. What made it unexpectedly useful?
When you need to truly recharge, how do you reboot after running in too many directions?
What's something you had to abandon to pursue something better?
Is there a place that means something significant in your story?
Let's imagine you had unlimited runway. What would you build or prove?
What's a thought or idea that keeps pulling at your attention these days?
If you could instantly master one skill, what would make you dangerous in the best way?
How do you handle pushback from people whose opinions actually matter to you?
Have you figured out anything about yourself recently that surprised you?
You're gifted a completely free afternoon. What do you actually enjoy when you're not chasing the next thing?
What's an inconvenient truth you've had to accept about yourself or the world?
What reliably flips your mood or energy in a good direction?
Is 'home' a place, a person, or a feeling for you? What does stability look like for someone who's always exploring?
Can you remember a conversation or debate that left a lasting mark on you?
What's something you keep doing even though you're clearly not optimized for it?
When was an impulsive move that turned out to be one of your best decisions?
What's an activity that absorbs you to the point where time disappears?
What's one area of yourself you're still trying to figure out?
Besides family, what relationship has pushed or shaped you in unexpected ways?
What's a question that would get past your clever deflection to something real?
In what area of your life are you trying to get more serious or intentional?
Do you have a personal practice you value, or one you think you'd actually stick with?
When you're feeling depleted, what gets you going again?
Tell me about something you made happen through persistent effort. Was it worth it?
If you could send a one-sentence message to your past self, what would have saved some pain?
What's something that both excites and terrifies you in equal measure?
If you could step back into one moment to experience it from scratch, which would you choose?
How do you learn to trust someone? What tells you they're intellectually honest enough?
What's one important thing that keeps getting bumped by more interesting distractions?
What's a stereotype about your generation that you think is totally wrong—or surprisingly right?
What's something you actually need but rarely admit or request?
What's a piece of recognition or feedback that hit you harder than you expected?
Imagine a version of your life where you stop second-guessing your own instincts. What changes?
What are two principles you argue for that sometimes contradict each other?
Is there a gap between your confident debate style and your actual uncertainty? (We all have one.)
Do you ever feel like you're performing a persona that doesn't capture your whole story?
Is there a 'clever, quick' version of yourself that you're tired of being?
Is there something from your past that you still feel weird about?
What's a past decision you keep mentally revisiting and relitigating?
Tell me about a part of yourself you've tried to argue away or suppress.
Is there a moment in your life you wish you could edit?
What's a feeling that runs under your wit that you don't often show?
Can you remember a time when being around people still left you feeling alone?
When it comes to the people you're closest to, what does it take for someone to actually get you?
What's a fundamental need you have that you struggle to ask for directly?
In what situations does the gap between how you come across and how you feel get widest?
Describe what real intellectual and emotional belonging would feel like.
Is there a quiet truth about yourself that you joke about but don't fully face?
Do you have a recurring thought that keeps circling back that you've never really addressed?
What's a belief you hold that you strategically avoid stating outright?
Is there something you're holding onto that logic says to let go of?
If your intuition could ask you one hard question right now, what do you think it would be?
